According to the press statement sent and sighted by The Ameh News (TAN) which was endorsed by Edward Adamu, Deputy Governor, Corporate Services and Osita Nwanisobi, Director, Corporate Communications both of the apex bank says the Central Bank of Nigeria the attention has been drawn to a FAKE PRESS RELEASE in circulation. The CBN stated that the fake press release which purported to have emanated from the Bank to the effect that President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the reissuance and release of old N500 and N1000 notes as legal tender in the country. “For the avoidance of doubt, the Central Bank of Nigeria reiterates that in line with the directives of Mr. President, only N200 old notes are to be reissued and to circulate concurrently with the new notes. Members of the public are therefore advised to ignore this fake news, it added. “The Bank is working with the law enforcement agencies to investigate, apprehend and prosecute the purveyors of this fake news, said CBN. 